<span class="header1">COMMUNICATIONS</span>
<p>Your ability to communicate may be your ticket into the occupations in this field. Those who work in this field are excellent communicators. They can speak in front of a large group of people.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Relations Specialist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/1369.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Relations Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Companies want customers and others to see them in a positive way.  So they hire people to see that this happens.  As a public relations specialist, you would let people know about the good things your company has done.  To do this, you would write press releases, brochures, and television and radio announcements.  It would be important that you were enthusiastic about the company. You would also need to be able to write and speak clearly.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in communications, journalism, or public relations for this job.  Work experience is important too.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $18,000 to $100,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Technical Writer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43289.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Technical Writer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Have you ever read the owner's manual for your computer, sound system, or video game? The person who wrote the manuals was a technical writer. In this job, you would write manuals, catalogs, and instruction books.  You would make science or technical information and directions easy for others to understand.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A college degree is needed for this job.  Usually the technical writer relies on a degree in a specialized field.  For example, writers who work on computer manuals usually have a degree in computer science.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary of a writer varies.  The amount would depend on what area of technology you were writing about.  It would also depend on whom you were working for.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Actor/Actress</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/C575061.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Actor/Actress" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you have a burning desire to be in the movies or in a play on Broadway, you might become a professional actor or actress.  In this job, you would play the role of a character in a play, television program, or movie.  To be successful, you must have a talent for acting.  You must also be able to perform in front of a large group of people. You would have to be able to remember your lines.  You would also have to get along with other actors, the directors, and others who make the production possible.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You can take college courses or get a degree in drama.  But the best teacher is experience. The courses give you a chance to learn new acting skills and improve your acting technique. But performing in front of an audience helps you to understand how to act.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>It is very difficult to say what an actor/actress makes.  Most actors do not have a steady job. In fact, they often take other jobs to make a living. It takes determination and hard work to be financially successful.  It can also take a long time.</blockquote>

