<span class="header1">CREATIVE TECHNOLOGY</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need people who can use their technical skills to create something new. Your creativity and interest in technology will help you to succeed in this field.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Photographer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43060.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Photographer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like taking pictures and have a good "eye," you might become a professional photographer. A photographer combines communications skills and technology.  In this job, you would take pictures of people, things, or events. You must be creative.  Your goal is to show people something they might otherwise not have seen.  You must understand the technical aspects of the camera.  You must know how to process film too. Many photographers work for themselves.  So, it is helpful to understand how a small business works.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A Bachelor's Degree in photography or the visual arts can develop your basic skills.  But, you also need to be creative to succeed in this field.  Spend as much time as possible looking at great pictures and taking your own. Getting involved in photography clubs and working in photo shops and labs will help you learn more about using your camera to capture successful photographs.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A photographer's salary can be anywhere from $15,000 to  $48,000 + per year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Video Editor</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/C506027.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Video Editor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When you watch a movie or television program, you are watching more than the work of actors.  You are watching the work of a video editor too.  As a video editor, you would use your creativity to piece together the footage of a film or program. You would have two goals.  You would want to be sure the audience could understand the story.  You also want to edit the film so that the audience could "feel" the movie.  You would use video equipment to make the movie seem exciting, dramatic, funny, or scary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>There are colleges that offer programs in video editing. You don't need a college degree to become a video editor, however, it will make a job easier to find.  Experience is very important.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A video editor's salary starts at around $28,000 and can go to over $100,000 in highly specialized areas.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Airbrush Artist</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As an airbrush artist, you would work in a photographic processing lab.  You would use your skills to restore damaged or faded photographs. To do this job well, you must understand the photo developing process. You must also like work that requires attention to detail.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>On-the-job training is provided for employees. Employers look for people who have a steady hand and an eye for detail.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average yearly salary is about $20,000.</blockquote>

