<span class="header1">TECHNOLOGY</span>
<p>If you prefer a hands-on approach in your work, you might be interested in occupations in this field.  You need to have skill in using technology.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Lighting Designer</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A lighting designer is a part of the stage crew that helps the actors look better on stage.  If you would like to be a part of a drama production, but not want to be an actor or director, this may be a job for you.  As a lighting designer, you would use your technical know-how to make the lighting on stage reflect the "feeling" of the play. For example, if the scene were set in the middle of an electrical storm you would make sure there were flashes of light on stage.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A Bachelor's Degree may help you to get a job, but it is not required.  It is important to have experience. Sometimes, lighting designers serve as an apprentice before becoming a designer. An apprentice is someone who is learning a trade by working on the job with an experienced person.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A yearly income of $15,000 to $150,000 may be earned.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Sound Mixer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43158.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Sound Mixer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A sound mixer makes the sound tracks for movies or television programs. If you would like to work in the movies or television without being in front of the camera, this job may be for you.  As a sound mixer, you would watch the movie or program and add music or sound effects. These sounds are important to the "feel" of the movie. You would make sure that the music and sound effects fit the scene. For example, the director may want a particular scene to be scary. You would add music and sound effects that would give the audience added reason to be scared.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>There is no educational requirement to be a sound mixer. Many sound mixers start their career by serving as an apprentice.  An apprentice is someone who is learning a trade by working on the job with an experienced person. Part-time jobs will be important in gaining needed experience.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary is based on skill and experience. A sound mixer may earn $20,000 to $100,000 a year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Road Manager</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43239.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Road Manager" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When rock bands or stage productions take their shows on the road, they hire a road manager. If you became a road manager, you would make the arrangements for equipment and performers to arrive at the concerts or performances on time. Road managers have a tough job.  They are expected to deal with any problems during a tour and to handle a thousand details.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>There is no college degree needed to be a road manager. You must have experience working with people and solving problems.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $15,000 to $100,000.</blockquote>

